  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;In&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;the absence of a Unilateral Undertaking or a Section 106 Agreement (S106) to secure appropriate rent levels in accordance with the Local Housing Allowance, the development would fail to secure the proposed HMO at an affordable rent level, contrary to Policy LP22(Houses in multiple occupancy) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-c93913b0-7fff-aaf4-52df-74af441aa280&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;In the absence of a Unilateral Undertaking or a Section 106 agreement securing appropriate mitigation by restricting future occupiers of the development from obtaining parking permits within the Controlled Parking Zone the proposed development would likely exacerbate existing parking stress and congestion on the surrounding highway network. The application is, therefore, contrary to Policy LP45 (Parking and Car Free Development) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Policy T6(Car parking)of the London Plan (2021).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;By&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-size: 10.5pt; white-space-collapse: preserve; text-align: justify; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;reason of the submitted Proposed Management Plan having failed to detail the length of tenancy agreements, licence renewal and management requirements the plan fails to be of a standard as required by Policy LP22(Houses in multiple occupancy) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "By&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-size: 10.5pt; white-space-collapse: preserve; text-align: justify; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;reason of the loss of existing housing suitable for family occupation, the proposed development would result in the undersupply of family sized dwellings in the borough, to the detriment of the borough’s identified housing need. As such, the development is contrary to Policies LP12(Meeting Housing Needs and Locations for New Homes) and LP22(Houses in multiple occupancy) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Policy H8(Loss of existing housing and estate redevelopment) of the London Plan (2021).&lt;/span&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;In&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;the absence of sufficient kitchen facilities and WCs for the proposed 8 bedroom (15 persons) HMO, the proposed HMO would fail to provide high quality accommodation, contrary to Policy LP22(Houses in multiple occupancy) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020) and the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-style: italic; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;Private Rented Property Licensing Accommodation Standards&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
